git

# Commands

## Branching
*Create branch*
git checkout -b <branch_name>

*Fix issue*
*Commit fix*

*Checkout master*
git checkout master

*Merge*
git merge <branch_name>

## Fork / Pull request
https://help.github.com/articles/fork-a-repo/
https://help.github.com/articles/syncing-a-fork/
https://help.github.com/articles/using-pull-requests/

## Fork workflow
*Fork via github gui*
git clone <original_repo.git>

*Create fetch upstream - optional*
git remote add upstream <original_repo.git>
git fetch upstream

*Check out local fork master*
git checkout master

*Merge upstream master into local master*
git merge upstream/master

*Fetch and merge via a Pull instead*
git pull upstream master

*Fix issue*
git branch <branch_name>
git checkout <branch_name>
OR
git checkout -b <branch_name>

*Push branch*
git push -u origin <branch_name>

*Create pull reuest via github gui*

*Delete branch*

## Push existing repository (after git init)
git remote add origin https://<repo>.git
git push -u origin master

## Tags
git tag -a [tag_name] -m ‘msg’
git push origin --tags
git push origin [tag_name]

# Create branch at tag
git checkout -b [branch_name] [tag_name]
